comment:
* Columns for tables that are synced to a server.
 * @deprecated Do not use.
 * @hide

variables.name: _SYNC_ACCOUNT
variables.comment:
* The account that was used to sync the entry to the device. *

Type: TEXT

variables.name: _SYNC_ACCOUNT_TYPE
variables.comment:
* The type of the account that was used to sync the entry to the device. *

Type: TEXT

variables.name: _SYNC_ID
variables.comment:
* The unique ID for a row assigned by the sync source. NULL if the row has never been synced. *

Type: TEXT

variables.name: _SYNC_TIME
variables.comment:
* The last time, from the sync source's point of view, that this row has been synchronized. *

Type: INTEGER (long)

variables.name: _SYNC_VERSION
variables.comment:
* The version of the row, as assigned by the server. *

Type: TEXT

variables.name: _SYNC_LOCAL_ID
variables.comment:
* Used in temporary provider while syncing, always NULL for rows in persistent providers. *

Type: INTEGER (long)

variables.name: _SYNC_MARK
variables.comment:
* Used only in persistent providers, and only during merging. *

Type: INTEGER (long)

variables.name: _SYNC_DIRTY
variables.comment:
* Used to indicate that local, unsynced, changes are present. *

Type: INTEGER (long)

variables.name: NON_SYNCABLE_ACCOUNT
variables.comment: * Used to indicate that this account is not synced

variables.name: NON_SYNCABLE_ACCOUNT_TYPE
variables.comment: * Used to indicate that this account is not synced
